    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I see. Two comments:\r\n\r\n- There is no reason why multithreading and TCP/IP networking should not be possible on truly embedded MCUs. Yes, it may be limited in terms of performance and memory availability, but no, this alone cannot explain why it shouldn't be possible.\r\n- MCUs actually **are** \"CPU & memory limited\", since an MCU contains a relatively simple CPU as well as a limited amout of memory. I cannot see why that statement wouldn't apply to MCU based systems..."
